-- Taiwan Stock-Market Movers: Epistar, Hannstar Display, Qisda
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-01-10T01:29:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/taiwan-stock-market-movers-epistar-hannstar-display-qisda.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual (TWSE)  moves in  Taiwan trading. (TWSE)  Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:18 a.m. local time in Taipei.  The Taiex Index rose 0.9 percent to 7,156.75, set for the
highest close since Dec. 1.  Epistar Corp. (2448)  (2448 TT) fell 1.6 percent to NT$62.30. The
light-emitting diode maker said December sales fell 22 percent
to NT$1.12 billion from a year earlier, according to a statement
to the Taiwan Stock Exchange.  Hannstar Display Corp. (6116)  (6116 TT) lost 2.7 percent to
NT$1.84, set for the biggest retreat since Dec. 19. The flat
panel maker said December sales dropped 26 percent to NT$2.51
billion from a year earlier, according to a statement to the
Taiwanese bourse.  Qisda Corp. (2352)  (2352 TT) increased 3.1 percent to NT$6.58, set
for the highest close since Dec. 5. The electronics maker’s
December sales rose 16 percent to NT$6.93 billion from a year
earlier, according to a statement to Taiwan’s exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
